<br>
Anyway, accept the fact that you don't belong here, and enjoy the game. I know I don't belong on FV, but I like it here for many other reasons so I'm staying. I'm not so insecure about my intentions or so guilt-riden that I have to manufacture a defense for it. It's very plain and simple. FV was launched for the roleplayers. I'm not a roleplayer, much. I'll respond in like context when presented with it, but I pretty much just want to do the exp hunt, dungeon crawling, video game part. I don't think I'm harming any true RPers game with my quiet style. I want to get to the end-game, but having been there before I'm not rushed to it. I'm rather enjoying the availability of all those low and mid level dungeons that I didn't do the first few times around. I think the RPers have to RP our presence because, right or wrong, we ain't leaving. Likewise, since the RPers are the only reason this server exists, we owe them utter courtesy and respect. They will eventually lose this server to us and the PGers to come, and that's pretty messed up for them.<br>
<br>
